NeWLY-ordained Chairman of Kaduna District of Cherubim and Seraphim Movement Church (CSMC) Worldwide Special Apostle Samuel Leke Samson and other ordained members of ‘Let’s Share the Grace’ (LSG) District have been advised to see their ordination as service to humanity. Senior Special Apostle Bisi Adedire, in a sermon: ‘A Call to Higher Height’, said ordination into positions within the vineyard of God should be seen as a call to service and not to be served. He urged them to also see their ordination as a call to higher heights accompanied by more responsibilities.   Rivers approves N8.2b for 10th flyover     Lagos ready to combat flooding, says Igbokwe     Council presents N3.1b budget   “We must all know that ordination is for service and not to be served. Some people think they shoud be served after they have been chosen and ordained, but it is not like that. ‘’Starting today, you must know that you are now into service to God and humanity. Service may not be so easy; it will require humility, perseverance, determination and sacrifice. Your ordination today is only telling you that you are now a servant of God called to serve his people. - Advertisement - “Ordination is not for jamboree or status upgrade, it is a call to higher heights, which also mean higher responsibilities. For every height a man attains, there are responsibilities’’. Adedire represented the Spiritual Father and Chairman of CSMC Worldwide Ayo ni o, Revd. Prophet Samuel Abidoye at the inauguration.